{"domain":"Collaboration","question":"A maintainer wants broad community Q&A without treating every post as a task. What should they use?","options":["GitHub Discussions","GitHub Issues","Required status checks","Blame view"],"answer":"GitHub Discussions","explanation":"Discussions are designed for open-ended conversation, Q&A, announcements, and ideas."},
{"domain":"Collaboration","question":"A pull request should automatically close issue #18 after it merges. Which description format is best?","options":["Use a closing keyword such as Fixes #18","Star the issue","Add #18 to .gitignore","Rename the branch to issue-18-only"],"answer":"Use a closing keyword such as Fixes #18","explanation":"Supported keywords such as fixes, closes, or resolves can link a pull request and close the issue when merged."},
